{
  "stem": "2833.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And a couple of days later at 2:00 or 3:00 in the morning, sometimes like this, they came and said we have to leave.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And that was when you could hear the-- it was the Russians who were close.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "You could hear already the, the, you know, shooting.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "So they took us on the-- down to train station, put us in cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "But we couldn't get through yet, so we had to stand on the station for three or four hours at least.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And during that time, the British bombed out that factory totally.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "They knew we were out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "They always knew exactly-- wherever a camp was, they knew.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And if you look, they never bombed any, any prisoner camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And they knew we were out, and they bombed that factory, which we still heard them talk about it while we were on the station.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And that is when they took us to Mauthausen, which is near Linz in Austria, and it's quite a trip.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And we had to go through Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And we always had to stay sometimes all night, sometimes only a few hours, waiting till there is a room for us to go on.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And that night, it was pouring rain.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And all we had was-- each car had one little soldier who had-- who was on the outside of the car in his little enclosure.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And we had one who was very young, and very-- he had lost an eye at the front, and so he was sent back and given that kind of duty.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And it was pouring rain and we knew he was in his little hut.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
